{"lemma":"مَسَّة","slug":"مَسَّة","root":"م.س.س","root_slug":"م-س-س","root_link":"/words/roots/م-س-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38541"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38541","headword_ar":"مَسَّهُ","root":"ms","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh,) first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masisotuhu","text_ar":"مَسِسْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) for which they sometimes say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misotuhu","text_ar":"مِسْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", rejecting the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, * S, M, * K,) and transferring the kesreh thereof to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, * S, M, *) contr. to general rule, (Sb, M,) and some do not transfer the kesreh, but leave the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"with its fethah, [saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masotuhu","text_ar":"مَسْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zilotumo","text_ar":"ظِلْتُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalotumo","text_ar":"ظَلْتُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalilotumo","text_ar":"ظَلِلْتُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", an irregular contraction, (S,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamas~uhu","text_ar":"يَمَسُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamosasohu","text_ar":"يَمْسَسْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when mejzoom, accord. to rule,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~N","text_ar":"مَسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiysN","text_ar":"مَسِيسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * M, A, K,) or the latter is a simple subst., (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mis~iysaY","text_ar":"مِسِّيسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * K;) and ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~ahu","text_ar":"مَسَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masasotuhu","text_ar":"مَسَسْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamus~uhu","text_ar":"يَمُسُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AO, S, M, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~N","text_ar":"مَسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) the former of which two verbs is the more chaste; (S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He touched it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"felt it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[generally the former,] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamasahu","text_ar":"لَمَسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with his hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA: as from the K [but wanting in a MS copy of the K and in the CK:]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he put his hand to it without the intervention of anything:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~N","text_ar":"مَسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamosN","text_ar":"لَمْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; excepting that the latter is [sometimes] used to signify the seeking for [or feeling for] a thing, even though it be not found; whereas the former is [only] said of that ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"action"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which is perception by the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lms","text_ar":"لمس"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Er-Rághib, TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamasahu","text_ar":"لَمَسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and [in like manner you say,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAs~a Al$~aYo'u Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"مَاسَّ الشَّىْءُ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mumaAs~apN","text_ar":"مُمَاسَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misaAsN","text_ar":"مِسَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, *) meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thing met"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"touched"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thing with its substance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~ahaA","text_ar":"مَسَّهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, Msb,) first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masisotuhaA","text_ar":"مَسِسْتُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamas~uhaA","text_ar":"يَمَسُّهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~N","text_ar":"مَسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiysN","text_ar":"مَسِيسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inivit eam;"},{"kind":"text","text":"scil. mulierem; (M, A, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAs~ahaA","text_ar":"مَاسَّهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mumaAs~apN","text_ar":"مُمَاسَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misaAsN","text_ar":"مِسَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the former is used in this sense in several places in the Kur, and is said by some to be preferable to the latter: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaAs~N","text_ar":"تَمَاسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used metonymically for [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming together, in the sense of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubaADaEapN","text_ar":"مُبَاضَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mumaAs~apN","text_ar":"مُمَاسَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~a AlmaA='u","text_ar":"مَسَّ المَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljasada","text_ar":"الجَسَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~N","text_ar":"مَسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water wetted the body."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~a","text_ar":"مَسَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, struck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smote;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because striking, or smiting, like touching, is with the hand. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~ahu","text_ar":"مَسَّهُ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2712},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAls~awoTi","text_ar":"بِالسَّوْطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck him with the whip"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b5-  And it is said of anything annoying or hurtful that befals a man. Thus in the Kur, [ii. 74, and iii. 23,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lano tamas~anaA Aln~aAru","text_ar":"لَنْ تَمَسَّنَا النَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"of hell"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will not smite us;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or here it may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"touch us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And [ii. 210,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~atohumu AlbaA^osaA='u","text_ar":"مَسَّتْهُمُ البَاْسَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"misfortune, smote,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afflicted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"befell, them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And in other instances; all which are similar to the saying in the same,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uwquwA mas~a saqara","text_ar":"ذُوقُوا مَسَّ سَقَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~N","text_ar":"مَسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.] You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~ahu AlmaraDu","text_ar":"مَسَّهُ المَرَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sickness smote him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"befell him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~ahu","text_ar":"مَسَّهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa*aAbu","text_ar":"العَذَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Punishment befell him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~ahu Alkibaru","text_ar":"مَسَّهُ الكِبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Old age came upon him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~atohu","text_ar":"مَسَّتْهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljin~u","text_ar":"الجِنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genii touched him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affected him with madness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insanity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) [whence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mus~a","text_ar":"مُسَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mus~a bihi","text_ar":"مُسَّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", app. meaning, from what immediately precedes,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mus~a","text_ar":"مُسَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAljunuwni","text_ar":"بِالجُنُونِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~N","text_ar":"مَسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"touched with madness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insanity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insane:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) as though the jinn had touched him. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~ahu biEa*aAbK","text_ar":"مَسَّهُ بِعَذَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He punished him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) ―         -b6-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~ato A_ilayohi AlHaAjapu","text_ar":"مَسَّتْ اـِلَيْهِ الحَاجَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n. ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~N","text_ar":"مَسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masiysN","text_ar":"مَسِيسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (assumed tropical:)  [which seems to signify either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The want of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was difficult of accomplishment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the want was difficult of accomplishment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressing, to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K,. [In both these lexicons, the meaning is left to be inferred only from the fact that this phrase immediately follows the explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjapN maAs~apN","text_ar":"حَاجَةٌ مَاسَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"q. v."},{"kind":"text","text":"]) ―         -b7-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~a","text_ar":"مَسَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also said of what is good, as well as of what is evil; as in the following instance:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~atohu mawaAs~u","text_ar":"مَسَّتْهُ مَوَاسُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayori waAl$~ar~i","text_ar":"الخَيْرِ وَالشَّرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The haps of good fortune, and of evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happened to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"betided him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-  [As touching implies proximity,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~ato bika raHimu","text_ar":"مَسَّتْ بِكَ رَحِمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The relationship of such a one is near to you."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA.) ―         -b9-  And as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~a","text_ar":"مَسَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"originally signifies “ he touched or felt with the hand, ” it is used metaphorically as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing; as, for instance, (in a trad.,) water from a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miyDaA^ap","text_ar":"مِيضَاَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mas~a","text_ar":"مَسَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made doubly trans. by means of the prep."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to the second objective complement. (Msb.) See 4, in two places."}],"source_refs":["A","Mgh","S","M","Msb","K","Sb","AO","TA"]}]}}